The management of The Nigerian Stock Exchange (The NSE) trading floor for the week under review shown the top three equities traded in Volume which was led by Linkage Assurance Plc, an insurance firm and two financial institutions (Skye Bank Plc and FCMB Group Plc), accounted for 809.798 million shares worth N1.130 billion in 2,551 deals, contributing 27.55 % and 4.04% to the total equity turnover volume and value respectively. Meanwhile, the overall total turnover of all transactions figures stood at 2.940 billion shares worth N27.924 billion in 28,570 deals were traded this week by investors on the floor of the Exchange in contrast to a total of 4.426 billion shares valued at N24.236 billion that exchanged hands last week in 29,573 deals. The report further disclosed the Financial Services Industry by volume led the activity chart with 2.174 billion shares valued at N17.033 billion traded in 19,013 deals; thus contributing 73.96% and 61.00% to the total equity turnover volume and value respectively. The Services Industry followed with 232.482 million shares worth N216.990 million in 734 deals. The third place was occupied by Conglomerates Industry with a turnover of 170.422 million shares worth N499.400 million in 1,578 deals. Also traded during the week shown a total of 25,586 units of Exchange Traded Products (ETPs) valued at N3.004 million executed in 11 deals, compared with a total of 1.200 million units valued at N6.951 million that was transacted last week in 10 deals. “A total of 2,785 units of Federal Government Bonds valued at N2.627 million were traded this week in 16 deals, compared with a total of 14,779 units valued at N14.050 million transacted last week in18 deals. “The NSE All-Share Index depreciated by 1.13% to close the week at 42,638.83 while Market Capitalization stood at N15.302 trillion respectively. Similarly, all other indices finished lower during the week with the exception of the NSE Pension Index that appreciated by 0.08% while the NSE ASeM Index closed flat Summary of price changes for the week shown thirty (30) equities appreciated in price during the week, higher than twenty-three (23)) of the previous week. While forty-eight (48) equities in other hand depreciated in price, lower than sixty-four (64) equities of the previous week leaving ninety-four (94) equities remained unchanged in price higher than eighty-five (85) equities recorded in the preceding week.